########################################################################################################################################
                                        From TCP/IP to POSIX, FreeBSD always innovate! 
                                   It servers the biggest and busiest sites on internet since 1999. 
                              FreeBSD is lightweight, robust, stable and very, very secure (CC/B3 EAL4). 
                              It has some exclusive technologies for perfomance, stability and security. 
                                 More details: https://www.freebsd.org/advocacy/whyusefreebsd.html
########################################################################################################################################
                         This template launches official FreeBSD AMI from AWS Market Place, currently 12.2. 
                        It uses IaC trought Terraform to implement customizations to the default image. 
                               The result is a high secure FreeBSD server on AWS EC2 by default. 
########################################################################################################################################
                           The first enhancements are about the instance launch, it's launched in a specific VPC,
                        with a specific subnet, some specific configurations and so on, avoiding human erros and 
                      ensuring that your AWS EC2 is running in the better possible way.
      More details can be found here: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Adiel-Ribeiro/Terraform/master/terraform-ec2-description
#########################################################################################################################################
             Besides the initial steps, this template goes above and beyond, it also configures the Operating System.
                This system allows SSH access, on non default port and all security options enabled by default. 
               It also has a custom kernel, wich disable everything unnecessary (services, proccess and drivers). 
                                   This hardened kernel is also optimized for AWS EC2.
         There are various other secutity configurations on system level to avoid misconfigurations or vulnerabilities. 
########################################################################################################################################
                    I suggest that you read all related files in this repository to understand all the changes. 
                            For in-depth details, please read init.sh script and freebsd-terraform-ec2.tf.
 There will be situations and scenarios that you should change some aspects from freebsd-terraform-ec2.tf, init.sh or even sshd_config.
                                              Fell free to do this and go ahead.
########################################################################################################################################
*********************************************************ATTENTION**********************************************************************
                                             Please, use sudo for daily tasks!!
                  After the launch proccess, don't be worried about the error message from Terraform: 
   Error: error executing "/tmp/terraform_1730798565.sh": wait: remote command exited without exit status or exit signal
       It's because the reboot action on your instance, you can just procceed and logon normally to your instance, enjoy!
